commentary: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Gulbadin Naib, OUT big nick! Or is it?! Given not out with Gulbadin driving well away from his body. Sarfaraz calls for the review! Seemed completely obvious live that he edged that ball but Nigel Llong didn't think so. Sarfaraz took an eternity to review overthinking things, i.e., was it so obvious that it wasn't an edge after all? Of course it was! Ultra-edge shows a clear spike when ball passes bat. Umpire Llong changes his signal.

commentary: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Hashmatullah Shahidi, OUT he's on a hat-trick! What a whirlwind over! Not the best ball to be fair. Full and angling down leg, should have been ticked through fine leg for four but Hashmatullah is out in front of the ball and his attempt to play it through the leg side results in a leading edge that balloons over Shaheen towards mid-off. Imad jogs 10 yards left and takes it at waist height in stride.

commentary: Shadab Khan to Asghar Afghan, OUT charges and will keep charging all the way to the pavilion! Possibly influenced by the silly point fielder in an effort to smash the ball and get him to go back to the circle, Asghar stampedes down the pitch to hammer a beautifully flighted ball on fifth stump. It holds it's line instead of turning and he's beaten trying to club this back over Shadab's head as the ball clips off stump. A promising stand ends.

commentary: Shadab Khan to Ikram Alikhil, no run uses his feet and is beaten by a very full ball prodding. Hit on the pads and Sarfaraz surprisingly goes for a review. Talked into it by Shadab. He was hit a long way down the pitch but was struck on the back pad in line with off stump as it beat him through the gap. Ball-tracking shows... umpire's call! Umpire Paul Wilson breathes a sigh of relief. That would have been the third overturned decision of the match and we're only just past the halfway point of the first innings. Pakistan retains their review though.

commentary: Imad Wasim to Ikram Alikhil, OUT the dot ball pressure on Ikram finally bursts! Floaty delivery at 84 kph/52 mph on about 7th/8th stump, just inside the wide guidelines, Ikram had to reach out a long way trying to slog this over long-on. Got more of the toe of the bat on it than middle and the ball loops in the air toward long-on. Simple catch taken at rib height 10 yards in from the rope.

commentary: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR runs Half-Man, Half-Amazing brings up the Afghanistan 200 with a glorious square drive! commentary: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Fakhar Zaman, OUT strikes second ball!. Given lbw but the batsman goes up to review. That looked out on first sight. Pitched on a length and spun in, carrom ball, beat his defensive prod to strike him on the pad. Bat and pad are very close to together, and there is a spike. I think it's of ball hitting pad, there's a gap between ball and bat. The third umpire's thinking the same. And ball tracking shows three reds! So not only have Pakistan lost Fakhar, they've lost a review too.

commentary: Rashid Khan to Sarfaraz Ahmed, 1 run, OUT runout! Pakistan are throwing this away! Googly lands way too short and wide on around 7th stump. Sarfaraz cut this behind point for a simple one, the point sweeper Najibullah is the quickest fielder of the XI for Afghanistan and the last guy Sarfaraz should be taking on. He circles around like a Blue Tiger to pounce, fire a sharp relay to Ikram with Sarfaraz five yards short. Never a second run there. Imad wasn't really interested and Sarfaraz only has himself to blame.
